reaching C++, providing defense-in-depth protection.\n\n## Comprehensive Test Coverage\n\ntest/parallel/test-child-process-reject-null-bytes.js (295 lines) provides regression tests for null byte validation covering:\n- Command string validation (exec, execSync) lines 19-37\n- File path validation (spawn, execFile, execFileSync, spawnSync, fork) lines 40-71\n- Arguments array validation (execFile, execFileSync, fork, spawn, spawnSync) lines 78-101\n- Current working directory validation (lines 104-138)\n- argv0 parameter validation (lines 140-175)\n- Shell parameter validation (lines 177-210)\n- Environment variable keys and values validation (lines 212-282)\n- execPath and execArgv validation for fork (lines 284-294)\n\nAll tests verify that ERR_INVALID_ARG_VALUE TypeError is thrown when null bytes are detected, preventing command injection attacks via string concatenation or argument manipulation."
